# Trivy vulnerability ignores — TEMPORARY and justified. Each entry MUST be removed once a fix ships.
# Trivy reads this file from the repo root (cwd) automatically, so it applies to every image scan
# (cd-aws.yml and cd.yml).
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-42504 — Go stdlib (net/textproto) malicious-MIME-header DoS, fixed in Go 1.26.4.
#
# This is baked into caddy's COMPILED binary in caddy:2-alpine (built with Go 1.26.3) — it is NOT an
# apk package, so it cannot be patched in-image (apk upgrade does not touch it). No caddy:2-alpine
# image rebuilt on Go >= 1.26.4 exists yet, so there is no shippable fix today.
#
# Risk accepted for the AWS experiment box (decided with the operator): caddy is reachable ONLY via
# the Cloudflare Tunnel (no public ports — see the deploy topology), which shrinks the DoS surface;
# and the flaw is a denial-of-service, not RCE. This is the ingress image only; the api image is
# unaffected (no Go binary).
#
# REMOVE this entry once caddy publishes an image built on Go >= 1.26.4 — a fresh re-tag will then
# pass the Trivy gate cleanly. Tracked as a follow-up task.
CVE-2026-42504
